# ── NEVER commit these ───────────────────────────────────────────
.secrets_cache.json
*.pyc
__pycache__/
.env
.env.*

# Both of these contain chat.js with a live API token baked in.
# They must NEVER be committed — GitHub push protection will block it.
#
# How the build works:
#   Local dev  → python chatbot_system.py build  → writes to docs/
#   CI/Actions → BUILD_OUTPUT_DIR=_site python … → writes to _site/
#
# _site/ is used in CI because upload-pages-artifact@v3 internally runs
# `git add` on the upload path — which exits 1 if the path is gitignored.
# So CI builds to _site/ (not gitignored at git-add time, just here for
# local safety) and uploads that. docs/ stays gitignored always.
docs/
_site/